Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake the chips on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

== Buffalo Sauce ==

Meanwhile, drain the @halloumi{225%g}, then cut widthways into 3 slices per person. Place them into a #small bowl{} of cold water and leave to soak.

Cut the @tomato{1%medium} into 1cm chunks.

Pop a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Pour in half the @cider vinegar{30%ml} and @water for the sauce{50%ml}. Bring to the boil, lower the heat and simmer until reduced by half, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the @sriracha sauce{15%ml} and @honey{15%ml}. Simmer until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}, then remove from the heat.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Stir through the @butter{20%g} until melted, then transfer to a small bowl. Wipe out the pan and keep it for later.

== Creamy Slaw ==

Remove the halloumi slices from the cold water, pop them onto a #plate{} lined with #kitchen paper{} and pat them dry.

In a #medium bowl{}, add the @coleslaw mix{120%g}, remaining cider vinegar and @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}. Season with salt and pepper, toss to combine and set aside.

== Assembly ==

When the chips have about ~{10%minutes} left, pop the (now empty) frying pan back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Once hot, add the halloumi, season with pepper and fry until golden, ~{2-3%minutes} each side.

Meanwhile, pop the @Greek style flatbreads{2} (1 per person) into the oven until warm, ~{3-4%minutes}.

When everything's ready, transfer the flatbreads to your plates and top with the @wild rocket{20%g} and tomato.

Lay the halloumi slices on top and drizzle over the buffalo sauce, then scatter over the @crumbled blue cheese{30%g}.

Serve the chips and coleslaw alongside.

Enjoy!